      "lesson title": "False Positives vs False Negatives in Manufacturing AI",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "In manufacturing, artificial intelligence systems are increasingly used to inspect products and flag potential defects, but these systems are not perfect. When an AI incorrectly rejects a good product, this is known as a false positive, and when it incorrectly accepts a faulty one, this is a false negative. Both types of error carry real costs for a business, whether that means wasted materials and lost output, or defective goods reaching customers. This lesson explores the practical difference between these two error types, why getting the balance right matters so much, and how manufacturers can make informed decisions about where to set their thresholds. By the end, you will have a clear and grounded understanding of how false positives and false negatives affect quality, efficiency, and the bottom line.",
