          "number": 7,
          "slidetitle": "Balancing Errors in Practice",
          "subtitle": "Striking the right balance every time",
          "slidecontent": "• Setting a threshold too high catches more defects but flags more good parts as faulty\n• Costs cut both ways\n• Every adjustment to sensitivity shifts the balance between missed faults and wasted product\n• Regular calibration using real production data keeps the model tuned to your actual environment\n• Cross-functional teams (quality, operations, and engineering) should review error rates together\n• Small threshold changes can have a surprisingly large impact on overall yield and customer satisfaction",
